SENATE AMENDMENT NO. ___
Offered by Of
Amend Senate Bill No. 1477 , Page 1 , Section TITLE , Line 3 ,
2 by striking "motorcycle auxiliary lighting" and inserting in
3 lieu thereof the following: "accessories of motor
4 vehicles"; and
5 Further amend said bill and page, section A, line 3, by
6 inserting after all of said line the following:
7 "301.472. 1. Any motor vehicle owner may receive
8 special license plates for any motor vehicle the person
9 owns, either solely or jointly, other than an apportioned
10 motor vehicle or a commercial motor vehicle licensed in
11 excess of twenty-four thousand pounds gross weight as
12 prescribed in this section after an annual payment of an
13 emblem-use authorization fee to a professional sports team
14 which has made an agreement pursuant to subsection 5 of this
15 section. For the purposes of this section a "professional
16 sports team" shall mean an organization located in this
17 state franchised by the National Professional Soccer League,
18 the National Women's Soccer League, the National Football
19 League, the National Basketball Association, the Women's
20 National Basketball Association, the National Hockey League,
21 the International Hockey League, or the American League or
22 the National League of Major League Baseball or a team
23 playing in Major League Soccer.
24 2. The professional sports team which has made an
25 agreement pursuant to subsection 5 of this section and which
1

6236S01.03S
26 receives the emblem-use authorization fee hereby authorizes
27 the use of its official emblem to be affixed on multiyear
28 personalized license plates as provided in this section.
29 Any vehicle owner may annually apply for the use of the
30 emblem. The director of revenue shall not authorize the
31 manufacturer of the material to produce such license plates
32 with the individual seal, logo, or emblem until the
33 department of revenue receives a minimum of one hundred
34 applications for each specific professional sports team.
35 3. Upon annual application and payment of a thirty-
36 five dollar emblem-use contribution to the professional
37 sports team such team shall issue to the vehicle owner,
38 without further charge, an emblem-use authorization
39 statement, which shall be presented by the owner to the
40 director of the department of revenue at the time of
41 registration of a motor vehicle. Upon presentation of the
42 annual statement and payment of a fifteen dollar fee in
43 addition to the regular registration fees, and presentation
44 of other documents which may be required by law, the
45 director shall issue a personalized license plate, which
46 shall bear the official emblem of the professional sports
47 team in a manner determined by the director. Such license
48 plates shall be made with fully reflective material with a
49 common color scheme and design, shall be clearly visible at
50 night, and shall be aesthetically attractive, as prescribed
51 by section 301.130. A fee for the issuance of personalized
52 license plates issued pursuant to section 301.144 shall not
53 be required for plates issued pursuant to this section.
54 4. A vehicle owner, who was previously issued a plate
55 with a professional sports team emblem authorized by this
56 section but who does not provide an emblem-use authorization
57 statement at a subsequent time of registration, shall be
2

6236S01.03S
58 issued a new plate which does not bear the professional
59 sports team emblem, as otherwise provided by law.
60 5. The director of the department of revenue is
61 authorized to make agreements with professional sports teams
62 on behalf of the state which allow the use of any such
63 team's official emblem pursuant to the provisions of this
64 section as consideration for receiving a thirty-five dollar
65 emblem-use contribution.
66 6. Except as provided in subsection 7 of this section,
67 a professional sports team receiving a thirty-five dollar
68 contribution shall forward such contribution, less an amount
69 not in excess of five percent of the contribution for the
70 costs of administration, to the Jackson County Sports
71 Authority or the St. Louis Regional Convention and Visitors
72 Commission. The moneys shall be administered as follows:
73 (1) The sports authority may retain not in excess of
74 five percent of all funds forwarded to it pursuant to this
75 section for the costs of administration and shall expend the
76 remaining balance of such funds, after consultation with a
77 professional sports team within the authority's area, on
78 marketing and promoting such team. The amount of money
79 expended from the funds obtained pursuant to this section by
80 the authority per professional sports team shall be in the
81 same proportion to the total funds available to be expended
82 on such team as the proportion of contributions forwarded by
83 the team to the authority is to the total contributions
84 received by the authority;
85 (2) The regional convention and visitors commission
86 shall hold the revenues received from the professional
87 sports teams in the St. Louis area in separate accounts for
88 each team. Each team may submit an annual marketing plan to
89 the commission. Expenses of a team which are in accordance
90 with the marketing plan shall be reimbursed by the
3

6236S01.03S
91 commission as long as moneys are available in the account.
92 The commission may retain not in excess of five percent for
93 the costs of administration. If no marketing plan is
94 submitted by a team, the commission shall market and promote
95 the team.
96 7. (1) The Kansas City Chiefs shall forward all
97 emblem-use fees received, less an amount not in excess of
98 five percent of the costs of administration, to the Chiefs'
99 Children's Fund, a not-for-profit fund established to
100 benefit children in need in the Kansas City area.
101 (2) The Kansas City Current shall forward all emblem-
102 use fees received, less an amount not in excess of five
103 percent of the costs of administration, to the Kansas City
104 Current Foundation or a team designated not-for-profit that
105 benefits youth in the Kansas City area.
106 8. The director of the department of revenue shall
107 promulgate rules and regulations for the administration of
108 this section. No rule or portion of a rule promulgated
109 pursuant to the authority of this section shall become
110 effective unless it has been promulgated pursuant to the
111 provisions of chapter 536."; and
112 Further amend the title and enacting clause accordingly.
